"Raindrops". The premiere of this waltz took place on 26 January 1902 at a festival concert in the Sofiensaal in Vienna in a vocal version for the Vienna Mens Choral Association. This waltz was an attempt by Ziehrer to depict the sound of rain in music, and was a great success when first played.

